race.comment: HOUSIE BOB (4) boasts a strong record this journey here with five wins and four minors from 15 tries. Missed the frame latest (23.40) when fourth over 400m at this track in a Grade 4/5. Looks a key chance on best form. SASSY SUPREME (6) failed to feature last start after losing her position early at Richmond, but prior to that won by 2.5 lengths at Richmond (35.80) beating Mickayla Swift in a Grade 5 on September 19. Comes out of a solid form race last start. Key runner on best form. SAIL AWAY SAM (1) looks close to another win after hitting the frame in a 4 length third (23.34) in a Grade 5 at this track. Has a very good strike-rate from this draw, with two wins from two starts. Well-placed to take this out. MAKE YOUR STAND (7) is worth including after a top-three finish in slick time most recently.
